WEBVTT

00:10.144 --> 00:12.546
- * ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:12.580 --> 00:13.647
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:13.681 --> 00:21.622
*

00:35.369 --> 00:38.839
- * CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:38.872 --> 00:46.280
*

00:46.314 --> 00:50.151
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:50.184 --> 00:53.587
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:53.621 --> 00:58.192
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:59.360 --> 01:01.629
[indistinct chatter]

01:01.662 --> 01:03.431
- HE'S NOT GETTING
INTO ANY MORE FIGHTS, IS HE?

01:03.464 --> 01:05.599
- OH, NO, NOTHING LIKE THAT.

01:05.633 --> 01:07.701
HUNTER HAS SHOWN
REMARKABLE PROGRESS.

01:07.735 --> 01:09.737
- THAT'S GOOD TO HEAR.

01:09.770 --> 01:11.305
- YES, HE'S EXTREMELY BRIGHT.

01:11.339 --> 01:12.840
- WELL, THAT RUNS
IN THE FAMILY.

01:12.873 --> 01:16.577
- HOWEVER, HE'S NOT
THE MOST DISCIPLINED STUDENT,

01:16.610 --> 01:19.213
AND HE HAS A TENDENCY
TO BE A BIT OF A...

01:19.247 --> 01:21.515
- SMART-ASS?

01:21.549 --> 01:23.384
RUNS IN THE FAMILY TOO.

01:23.417 --> 01:26.254
- BUT YOU'RE TO BE COMMENDED
FOR DOING AN EXCELLENT JOB.

01:26.287 --> 01:28.856
- AH, THANK YOU, MS. CROWE.

01:28.889 --> 01:31.859
- THANK YOU.

01:31.892 --> 01:33.361
DID YOU HEAR THAT?
THAT'S THE FIRST TIME A TEACHER

01:33.394 --> 01:35.196
HAS EVER GIVEN ME
AN "EXCELLENT."

01:35.229 --> 01:37.131
- [chuckles]

01:38.499 --> 01:41.202
- EXCUSE US.

01:41.235 --> 01:42.470
ARE YOU HUNTER'S PARENTS?

01:42.503 --> 01:43.537
- YES, THAT'S RIGHT.

01:43.571 --> 01:45.406
- WE'RE CALLIE'S FOLKS.

01:45.439 --> 01:47.241
- UH, CALLIE...

01:47.275 --> 01:48.876
- OUR KIDS
ARE SEEING ONE ANOTHER.

01:48.909 --> 01:51.279
- YES, OF COURSE,
THE FAMOUS CALLIE.

01:51.312 --> 01:53.347
- STEVE LEESON.
- AMBER MORGAN-LEESON.

01:53.381 --> 01:56.384
- BEN BRUCKNER.
- MICHAEL NOVOTNY-BRUCKNER.

01:56.417 --> 01:59.353
- HUNTER ALWAYS SPEAKS OF YOU
BOTH WITH SUCH ADMIRATION.

01:59.387 --> 02:00.921
- HE DOES?
- WELL, YOU KNOW HOW KIDS ARE.

02:00.954 --> 02:02.656
THEY'LL NEVER TELL YOU
TO YOUR FACE.

02:02.690 --> 02:04.225
- YEAH.
- MM.

02:04.258 --> 02:05.426
- CALLIE'S LIKE
A LITTLE SCHOOLGIRL

02:05.459 --> 02:07.261
EVERY TIME
SHE MENTIONS HIS NAME.

02:07.295 --> 02:09.630
- SHE IS A SCHOOLGIRL.
[laughter]

02:09.663 --> 02:11.365
- YOU SHOULD BE VERY PROUD.
HE'S A VERY NICE YOUNG MAN.

02:11.399 --> 02:13.634
- I THINK HE'D PREFER
"COOL DUDE."

02:13.667 --> 02:14.768
- [chuckles]

02:14.802 --> 02:16.404
LISTEN, UH, WE WOULD LOVE

02:16.437 --> 02:17.905
TO GET TOGETHER
WITH YOU GUYS.

02:17.938 --> 02:20.241
- THAT'D BE GREAT.
- I'LL BE IN TOUCH.

02:20.274 --> 02:21.442
WE'LL PLAN AN EVENING.
- TERRIFIC.

02:21.475 --> 02:23.277
- OKAY.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

02:23.311 --> 02:26.146
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- BYE-BYE.

02:34.322 --> 02:37.391
- HOW DOES THAT FEEL?

02:37.425 --> 02:39.693
- IT'D BE A LOT BETTER
WITH POPPERS.

02:39.727 --> 02:41.662
- TRY TO DESCRIBE
THE SENSATION.

02:41.695 --> 02:46.200
- IT FEELS AS IF SOMEONE
IS ROTATING MY ARTIFICIAL BALL.

02:47.901 --> 02:49.703
- [sighs]
PLEASE.

03:01.782 --> 03:04.218
YOU'VE PUT ON SOME WEIGHT.

03:04.252 --> 03:05.953
- I REALIZE TO YOU
THAT'S A GOOD THING.

03:05.986 --> 03:08.489
TO ME, IT'S A DISASTER.

03:08.522 --> 03:11.459
- YOU CAN DRESS NOW.

03:14.262 --> 03:15.496
- SO WHAT'S THE VERDICT?

03:15.529 --> 03:17.331
- ARE YOU STILL
EXPERIENCING FATIGUE?

03:17.365 --> 03:18.766
- NOT AS MUCH.

03:18.799 --> 03:19.833
- HOW'S YOUR SEX DRIVE?

03:19.867 --> 03:21.335
- WITH BOTH HANDS ON THE WHEEL.

03:21.369 --> 03:22.870
- MM-HMM.

03:22.903 --> 03:25.773
OF COURSE, UM,
WE CAN'T BE CERTAIN

03:25.806 --> 03:26.974
THAT EVEN WITHIN A MONTH
OR A YEAR

03:27.007 --> 03:28.609
THAT THE CANCER
WON'T REOCCUR.

03:28.642 --> 03:31.379
BUT THE, UH, SONOGRAM
AND THE BLOOD TESTS

03:31.412 --> 03:33.614
SHOW NO SIGNS OF SPREADING.

03:33.647 --> 03:35.716
- HOW LONG TILL
I CAN RESUME A NORMAL LIFE,

03:35.749 --> 03:37.017
DOING RECREATIONAL DRUGS

03:37.050 --> 03:39.887
AND CONSUMING VAST AMOUNTS
OF ALCOHOL?

03:39.920 --> 03:41.722
GOING TO THE GYM?

03:41.755 --> 03:43.491
- I DON'T HAVE ANY PROBLEM
WITH SOME LIGHT STRETCHING

03:43.524 --> 03:44.858
AND MILD CARDIO.

03:44.892 --> 03:46.994
- DOC, I'M A FAG.

03:47.027 --> 03:48.862
I DON'T GO TO THE GYM
TO BE HEALTHY.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.598
I GO THERE TO LOOK GOOD.

03:50.631 --> 03:53.033
LIGHT STRETCHING AND MILD CARDIO
AREN'T GOING TO CUT IT.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.002
- BRIAN, YOU'VE HAD CANCER.

03:55.035 --> 03:58.272
YOUR BODY'S BEEN THROUGH A
SERIES OF RADIATION TREATMENTS.

03:58.306 --> 04:01.875
I SUGGEST YOU TAKE IT EASY,
GIVE YOURSELF TIME TO RECOVER.

04:01.909 --> 04:04.645
AFTER ALL, YOU'RE, UH,
NOT 21 ANYMORE.

04:09.850 --> 04:12.019
- THIS IS
A FUCKING CATASTROPHE.

04:12.052 --> 04:14.388
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED
TO JEFFREY PENDERGRASS?

04:14.422 --> 04:16.490
- HE FELT
HE DIDN'T HAVE THE SUPPORT

04:16.524 --> 04:19.427
OF CERTAIN INFLUENTIAL MEMBERS
OF THE COMMUNITY

04:19.460 --> 04:21.028
AND THAT,
WITHOUT THEIR BACKING,

04:21.061 --> 04:23.364
HE COULDN'T SUCCESSFULLY
MEET THE GOALS.

04:23.397 --> 04:24.832
- SO HE TOOK OFF,

04:24.865 --> 04:26.834
WITH PRACTICALLY EVERY CENT
WE MANAGED TO RAISE.

04:26.867 --> 04:28.369
- BASTARD!
- WE AGREED TO PAY

04:28.402 --> 04:29.537
ALL HIS EXPENSES.

04:29.570 --> 04:31.772
- INCLUDING HOTEL SUITE,
CHAMPAGNE,

04:31.805 --> 04:33.574
AND THE KICK-OFF PARTY
AT BABYLON?

04:33.607 --> 04:35.409
- WHICH IT BARELY MANAGED
TO COVER, ACCORDING TO HIM.

04:35.443 --> 04:38.979
- UGH, I GUESS BRIAN
HAD HIS NUMBER ALL ALONG.

04:39.012 --> 04:40.448
- OKAY, SO WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

04:40.481 --> 04:42.650
- THERE'S ONLY ONE THING
WE CAN DO--

04:42.683 --> 04:45.786
CANCEL THE LIBERTY RIDE,
REFUND EVERYONE'S MONEY.

04:45.819 --> 04:47.721
- HOW CAN YOU REFUND IT
IF YOU HAVEN'T GOT IT?

04:47.755 --> 04:49.957
- HOW MUCH ARE WE IN THE HOLE?

04:49.990 --> 04:52.660
- ALMOST $25,000.

04:52.693 --> 04:55.863
[all groan]

04:55.896 --> 04:57.665
- CONGRATULATIONS,
EVERYONE,

04:57.698 --> 05:00.368
ON BEING THE FIRST CHARITY RIDE
TO PEDAL BACKWARDS.

05:00.401 --> 05:01.935
- LOOK, LIBERTY HOUSE
IS DEPENDING ON US.

05:01.969 --> 05:04.004
WITHOUT THIS RIDE, THEY'LL BE
FORCED TO CLOSE THEIR DOORS.

05:04.037 --> 05:07.741
- THEN WE HAVE NO CHOICE
BUT TO GO AHEAD WITH IT.

05:07.775 --> 05:11.612
- AND HOPE THAT WE FIND
MORE PLEDGES AND SPONSORS.

05:13.981 --> 05:16.417
- IT'S AWFULLY SWEET OF YOU,
TEDDY, TO TAKE ME TO LUNCH.

05:16.450 --> 05:18.552
- WELL, I FIGURED YOU COULD USE
SOME CHEERING UP.

05:18.586 --> 05:21.455
- I HAVE TO ADMIT,
IT HASN'T BEEN EASY.

05:21.489 --> 05:23.557
AFTER ALL,
HOW MANY TIMES IN LIFE

05:23.591 --> 05:25.626
DO YOU GET TO LIVE OUT
A FANTASY?

05:25.659 --> 05:28.829
YOU KNOW,
HAVE A SECRET AFFAIR

05:28.862 --> 05:32.366
WITH A FAMOUS FOOTBALL STAR,

05:32.400 --> 05:35.436
HAVE HIM RIDE YOUR BACK END
THREE TIMES A WEEK

05:35.469 --> 05:37.971
WITH HIS ROCK-HARD,
10-INCH BATTERING RAM

05:38.005 --> 05:42.743
UNTIL YOUR SCREAMS OF ECSTASY
FILL AN ENTIRE STADIUM?

05:42.776 --> 05:44.845
TO LIE THERE SPENT,

05:44.878 --> 05:48.115
EXHAUSTED, INSENSATE?

05:48.148 --> 05:50.451
AND THAT'S ONLY HALFTIME.
[chuckles]

05:50.484 --> 05:53.387
- NOT OFTEN.
SO WHAT ARE YOU IN THE MOOD FOR?

05:53.421 --> 05:55.389
- I COULD DO
WITH A CHINESE CHICKEN SALAD...

05:55.423 --> 05:58.992
AND WITHOUT ANY MORE TALK
OF DREW BOYD.

05:59.026 --> 06:00.561
- [sighs]

06:00.594 --> 06:02.129
IN THAT CASE,

06:02.162 --> 06:05.766
YOU MAY WANT TO AVOID
MAJOR THOROUGHFARES.

06:09.102 --> 06:11.605
ALL FORMS
OF PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION,

06:11.639 --> 06:14.608
BETTER SHOPS
AND DEPARTMENT STORES.

06:14.642 --> 06:16.510
I'D ALSO STAY AWAY
FROM PUBLICATIONS

06:16.544 --> 06:20.013
SUCH AS NEWSPAPERS
AND MAGAZINES FOR, UH...

06:20.047 --> 06:22.616
OH, UH, A YEAR OR SO.

06:22.650 --> 06:27.421
AND, UH, DON'T LOOK UP.

06:27.455 --> 06:30.023
- [sighs]

06:30.057 --> 06:34.795
[whining]
GOUGE MY EYES OUT NOW.

06:34.828 --> 06:37.465
- POOR THING.

06:41.569 --> 06:45.573
[indistinct chatter]

06:45.606 --> 06:48.676
- YOU LOOK
ABSOLUTELY RADIANT, MEL.

06:48.709 --> 06:50.511
- LIKE A BOTTICELLI MADONNA.

06:50.544 --> 06:52.913
- I WAS THINKING MORE LIKE
A RINGLING BROTHERS ELEPHANT.

06:52.946 --> 06:56.183
- THIS MUST BE THE HAPPIEST TIME
OF YOUR LIFE.

06:56.216 --> 06:57.518
- MUST BE.

06:57.551 --> 06:59.520
- HI, EVERYONE.

06:59.553 --> 07:01.188
- HEY, LINDSAY.

07:01.221 --> 07:04.692
- SORRY I'M LATE.
- LAST-MINUTE AUERBACH SALE?

07:04.725 --> 07:06.660
- YOU WANT SOME FRUIT PUNCH?

07:06.694 --> 07:09.863
I'VE ALSO GOT GINGER ALE
OR VANILLA SOY DRINK.

07:09.897 --> 07:11.532
- I WISH THEY'D LOWER
THE DRINKING AGE TO FIVE.

07:11.565 --> 07:12.933
I COULD SURE USE A SCOTCH.

07:12.966 --> 07:14.802
- CONGRATULATIONS ON THE SHOW
AT THE GALLERY.

07:14.835 --> 07:16.937
- HEY, IT'S BEEN ALL OVER
THE PAPERS.

07:16.970 --> 07:18.539
- THAT MUST'VE BEEN
A REAL THRILL,

07:18.572 --> 07:20.941
WORKING WITH A FAMOUS ARTIST
LIKE SAM AUERBACH.

07:20.974 --> 07:23.076
- YOU CAN'T IMAGINE
HOW ATTENTIVE SHE WAS,

07:23.110 --> 07:26.446
TENDING TO HIS EVERY NEED.

07:35.589 --> 07:37.257
- WAS THAT REMARK
REALLY NECESSARY?

07:37.290 --> 07:40.494
- HMM? WHAT REMARK?
- YOU KNOW WHAT REMARK--

07:40.528 --> 07:42.229
ABOUT MY ATTENDING
TO HIS EVERY NEED.

07:42.262 --> 07:43.964
- IT'S TRUE, ISN'T IT?

07:43.997 --> 07:46.967
IN FACT, I'M SURPRISED
YOU EVEN BOTHERED TO COME.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.136
- WHY WOULDN'T I?
- NOT A MAN IN SIGHT...

07:49.169 --> 07:50.504
JUST US DYKES.

07:50.538 --> 07:51.839
- LOOK, I TOLD YOU
HOW SORRY I AM,

07:51.872 --> 07:53.173
THAT IT WAS A MISTAKE.

07:53.206 --> 07:55.709
- ACTUALLY, YOU SAID
IT WAS A GOOD THING.

07:55.743 --> 07:57.144
- I NEVER SAID
IT WAS A GOOD THING.

07:57.177 --> 07:59.112
- THAT IT GAVE YOU A CHANCE
TO CONTRAST AND COMPARE

07:59.146 --> 08:02.115
AND COME TO THE CONCLUSION
THAT, GIVEN THE CHOICES,

08:02.149 --> 08:03.283
YOU STILL PREFER ME.

08:03.316 --> 08:04.618
- THAT PART IS TRUE.

08:04.652 --> 08:05.853
- WELL, IT ISN'T TRUE FOR ME.

08:05.886 --> 08:07.721
I KNOW WHICH TEAM I PLAY ON.

08:07.755 --> 08:09.590
IT'S NOT A CHOICE
OR A PREFERENCE.

08:09.623 --> 08:12.059
IT'S WHO I AM.
IT'S WHO I'VE ALWAYS BEEN--

08:12.092 --> 08:13.761
A RUG-MUNCHER,
A MUFF-DIVER,

08:13.794 --> 08:15.863
A CUNT-LAPPER, A BULL,
A LEZZIE, A DYKE.

08:15.896 --> 08:17.297
- WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM?

08:17.330 --> 08:18.766
- DON'T ASK ME TO MAKE UP
YOUR MIND FOR YOU.

08:18.799 --> 08:19.933
YOU HAVE TO DO THAT
ALL BY YOURSELF.

08:19.967 --> 08:21.669
- I'M A LESBIAN.

08:21.702 --> 08:23.737
- NOT IF YOU'RE HAVING SEX
WITH A MAN, HONEY...

08:23.771 --> 08:26.139
WHILE I'M PREGNANT, YET.

08:26.173 --> 08:30.510
I DON'T KNOW WHICH BETRAYAL
TO NEVER FORGIVE YOU FOR FIRST.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.150
- BAD TIMING?
- NO.

08:37.184 --> 08:39.086
WE WERE JUST HAVING
A DISCUSSION.

08:39.119 --> 08:40.287
- YOU DON'T HAVE
TO EXPLAIN IT TO ME.

08:40.320 --> 08:41.789
I'VE HAD THREE.

08:41.822 --> 08:43.023
THERE'S NOTHING
LIKE A GOOD PREGNANCY

08:43.056 --> 08:44.958
TO TURN YOU
INTO A RAVING BITCH.

08:52.666 --> 08:53.901
- THIS GUY PENDERGRASS
SKIPPED TOWN,

08:53.934 --> 08:55.335
LEAVING THE CENTER
HIGH AND DRY?

08:55.368 --> 08:56.904
- THAT'S ABOUT
THE LONG AND SHORT OF IT.

08:56.937 --> 08:59.172
- YEAH, MORE THE SHORT OF IT,
AS IN CASH.

08:59.206 --> 09:01.108
- I WONDER WHAT HAPPENED.

09:01.141 --> 09:02.910
- WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING
AT ME FOR?

09:02.943 --> 09:04.177
- IT DOESN'T MATTER--
WE'RE STILL GOING TO TRAIN,

09:04.211 --> 09:06.079
AND WE'RE STILL
GOING TO RIDE.

09:06.113 --> 09:07.848
- YOU COMING IN WITH US?

09:07.881 --> 09:09.983
- OH, BRIAN'S DOCTOR CAUTIONED
HIM TO TAKE IT EASY.

09:10.017 --> 09:11.318
- MEANING WHAT--

09:11.351 --> 09:13.921
GETTING LAID THREE TIMES A WEEK
INSTEAD OF FOUR?

09:13.954 --> 09:15.656
- MORE LIKE SEVEN
INSTEAD OF NINE.

09:15.689 --> 09:17.057
- YEAH, SOME RECUPERATION.

09:17.090 --> 09:18.959
- TOO BAD
YOU CAN'T GO WITH US.

09:18.992 --> 09:20.728
- EVEN IF HE WAS
IN PEAK CONDITION,

09:20.761 --> 09:23.931
I DOUBT BRIAN WOULD BE DONATING
HIS BACKSIDE FOR CHARITY.

09:23.964 --> 09:25.799
- IT'S NOT JUST A CHARITY.

09:25.833 --> 09:27.935
WE ALL KNOW SOMEONE,
OR AT LEAST HEARD OF SOMEONE,

09:27.968 --> 09:30.070
WHO SPENT HIS LAST DAYS
AT LIBERTY HOUSE.

09:30.103 --> 09:32.940
SOMEDAY IT MIGHT BE ONE OF US.

09:32.973 --> 09:34.675
- NOT AS LONG AS I'M AROUND.

09:34.708 --> 09:37.210
- THE POINT IS, WE ALL DESERVE
TO DIE WITH DIGNITY

09:37.244 --> 09:39.212
AND A FRIEND BY OUR SIDE.

09:39.246 --> 09:41.081
- I'M SURE EVEN BRIAN
WOULD AGREE WITH THAT.

09:41.114 --> 09:42.249
- HMM.

09:45.653 --> 09:47.721
- SEE YA.
- BYE, BRIAN.

09:47.755 --> 09:49.089
- SEE YA.

09:49.122 --> 09:51.258
- [clears throat]

09:53.193 --> 09:56.296
- WHAT'S UP?

09:56.329 --> 09:59.833
- THIS BIG, BLACK S.U.V.
HAS BEEN CIRCLING THE BLOCK.

09:59.867 --> 10:02.269
IT KEEPS STOPPING
IN FRONT OF THE HOUSE.

10:02.302 --> 10:03.971
CHRIST, NOW IT'S PARKING.

10:04.004 --> 10:07.374
- SO?
- WELL, I DON'T LIKE IT.

10:07.407 --> 10:11.144
I DON'T LIKE IT AT ALL.

10:11.178 --> 10:14.882
YOU DON'T SUPPOSE VIC
HAD A SECRET LIFE, DO YOU?

10:14.915 --> 10:16.383
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
MAYBE HE WORKED FOR THE CIA

10:16.416 --> 10:19.119
OR THE MAFIA
OR SOME FOREIGN GOVERNMENT,

10:19.152 --> 10:22.155
AND NOW THAT HE'S GONE,
THEY DECIDED TO RUB US OUT?

10:25.158 --> 10:27.895
- NO.

10:27.928 --> 10:31.198
- WELL, I HAVE TO GO TO WORK,
AND I'M AFRAID TO GO OUT THERE.

10:31.231 --> 10:34.301
- YOU USE THE BACK WAY.
I'LL DISTRACT THEM.

10:34.334 --> 10:36.436
- GOOD IDEA.

10:36.469 --> 10:40.974
- BUT I'M TELLING CARL
ABOUT THIS, JUST IN CASE.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.973
- IF YOU'RE PLANNING
TO ACCOST ME,

11:13.006 --> 11:15.776
YOU SHOULD KNOW, THEY DON'T
CALL US SCREAMING FAGGOTS

11:15.809 --> 11:17.177
FOR NOTHING.

11:17.210 --> 11:18.946
AND IF YOU'RE HOPING TO SCORE,

11:18.979 --> 11:21.081
YOU'RE GOING ABOUT IT
ALL WRONG.

11:24.818 --> 11:27.855
- GET IN.

11:27.888 --> 11:30.223
- I DON'T ACCEPT RIDES
FROM STRANGERS...

11:30.257 --> 11:31.959
PARTICULARLY THOSE
WHO DON'T SHOW UP

11:31.992 --> 11:33.360
OR AT LEAST CALL.

11:33.393 --> 11:36.163
- GET IN.

11:49.176 --> 11:51.378
- NICE OIL TANKER.

11:51.411 --> 11:54.114
SO WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO QUEERSVILLE?

11:54.147 --> 11:56.349
- MY GAME'S BEEN SHIT.
- MM? TALK TO YOUR COACH.

11:56.383 --> 11:57.951
- I CAN'T SLEEP.
- TAKE A XANAX.

11:57.985 --> 12:00.854
- I'M DRINKING TOO MUCH.
- BUY MORE BEER NUTS.

12:03.190 --> 12:05.759
- I MISS YOU.

12:07.394 --> 12:10.263
- YOU DO?

12:13.934 --> 12:15.769
- CAN WE GO TO THE MOTEL?

12:15.803 --> 12:18.839
- YEAH.

12:18.872 --> 12:20.841
UM...NO.

12:20.874 --> 12:24.044
NO, I-I CAN'T GO BACK THERE.

12:24.077 --> 12:25.512
- I THOUGHT YOU LOVE
WHEN I FUCK YOU.

12:25.545 --> 12:28.548
- I DO LOVE
WHEN YOU FUCK ME.

12:28.581 --> 12:30.250
THIS ISN'T THE ATKINS DIET.

12:30.283 --> 12:32.986
YOU KNOW, MAN CAN'T LIVE
ON MEAT ALONE...

12:33.020 --> 12:36.289
AT LEAST THIS MAN CAN'T.

12:42.595 --> 12:45.298
- ALL RIGHT, WE'LL GO OUT.

12:47.200 --> 12:50.303
- YOU MEAN IT?

12:55.075 --> 12:56.409
CAREFUL.

12:56.443 --> 12:58.311
WHAT IF SOMEBODY SEES US?

12:58.345 --> 13:00.981
- THEY CAN'T.

13:01.014 --> 13:03.183
[knocks on window]

13:03.216 --> 13:05.552
REMEMBER?

13:05.585 --> 13:08.455
- [chuckles]

13:18.331 --> 13:22.335
[moaning]

13:24.938 --> 13:28.441
- YOU HAVE NICE LIPS,
REALLY SOFT.

13:28.475 --> 13:32.245
- THANKS. YOU TOO.

13:32.279 --> 13:34.581
- THEY'RE THE FIRST THING
I NOTICED ABOUT YOU.

13:34.614 --> 13:37.117
- YEAH?
- YEAH.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.052
WHAT WAS THE FIRST THING
YOU NOTICED ABOUT ME?

13:39.086 --> 13:42.055
- HMM...YOUR NOSE.
[laughs]

13:42.089 --> 13:45.025
- YOU LIAR.

13:48.996 --> 13:51.965
THESE.

14:02.442 --> 14:06.213
- DID I ALSO MENTION
YOU HAVE A REALLY CUTE ASS?

14:06.246 --> 14:09.149
[both laughing]

14:30.437 --> 14:32.105
DO YOU HAVE A CONDOM?

14:32.139 --> 14:35.108
- HUH?
- A CONDOM.

14:35.142 --> 14:36.509
- I KNOW WHAT IT IS.

14:36.543 --> 14:37.978
- WELL, IF YOU DON'T,
I APPROPRIATED SOME

14:38.011 --> 14:40.948
FROM MY BROTHER.

14:42.715 --> 14:43.984
- YOU REALLY WANT TO?

14:44.017 --> 14:47.520
- WELL, DON'T YOU?

14:47.554 --> 14:50.991
- SURE.

14:51.024 --> 14:53.994
IT'S JUST THAT...

14:54.027 --> 14:57.197
BEFORE WE DO...

14:57.230 --> 15:01.001
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD KNOW.

15:02.702 --> 15:06.273
I'M POSITIVE.

15:06.306 --> 15:09.142
- POSITIVE?

15:09.176 --> 15:10.210
YOU MEAN...

15:10.243 --> 15:13.013
- I HAVE H.I.V.

15:13.046 --> 15:15.682
- SHIT.
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

15:15.715 --> 15:18.185
- I'M NOT SICK OR ANYTHING.

15:18.218 --> 15:20.287
IT'S JUST...

15:20.320 --> 15:22.555
THERE...

15:22.589 --> 15:25.558
INSIDE ME.

15:25.592 --> 15:29.096
- HOW DID YOU GET IT?

15:29.129 --> 15:33.466
WAS IT A TRANSFUSION
OR FROM DOING DRUGS?

15:37.204 --> 15:39.639
- IT'S OKAY.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TELL ME.

15:39.672 --> 15:42.742
DOES ANYONE ELSE
AT SCHOOL KNOW?

15:42.775 --> 15:45.112
- UH, NO.

15:45.145 --> 15:49.316
- I PROMISE
I WON'T TELL ANYONE.

15:49.349 --> 15:51.384
I'M SORRY.

15:51.418 --> 15:55.088
- YEAH.

15:55.122 --> 15:58.491
I GUESS I BETTER GO.

16:04.097 --> 16:07.634
- WAIT.

16:07.667 --> 16:10.637
MY PARENTS WON'T BE HOME
FOR A COUPLE OF HOURS.

16:10.670 --> 16:14.341
- BUT I THOUGHT--
- WELL...

16:14.374 --> 16:17.144
WE HAVE THESE, DON'T WE?

16:17.177 --> 16:21.114
AS LONG AS WE USE ONE,
THEN IT'S SAFE, RIGHT?

16:49.409 --> 16:51.511
- [sighs]

16:51.544 --> 16:53.113
I THOUGHT WE AGREED
YOU WERE GOING TO AVOID

16:53.146 --> 16:56.516
ALL MAJOR THOROUGHFARES,
STORES, AND PUBLICATIONS.

16:56.549 --> 16:58.318
- I KNOW.
- YOU HAVE TO BE STRONG, EM.

16:58.351 --> 16:59.786
OKAY?
SITTING HERE, PINING AWAY,

16:59.819 --> 17:01.788
SIPPING ICE CREAM SODAS
IS NO SOLUTION.

17:01.821 --> 17:04.157
YOU NEED TO SHIFT YOUR FOCUS.

17:04.191 --> 17:06.293
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:10.563 --> 17:13.266
- GOD, I WISH THERE WAS A
MEETING YOU COULD GO TO TONIGHT.

17:13.300 --> 17:15.602
- WELL, I CAN'T.

17:15.635 --> 17:17.270
DREW'S TAKING ME OUT...

17:17.304 --> 17:19.072
ON A REAL DATE.

17:19.106 --> 17:20.540
I'M FINALLY GOING TO SEE
SOMETHING BESIDES THE CEILING

17:20.573 --> 17:23.843
OF ROOM 12
AT THE HACIENDA MOTEL.

17:23.876 --> 17:25.578
- I THOUGHT YOU AND HE
BROKE UP.

17:25.612 --> 17:27.747
- HE MISSED ME.

17:27.780 --> 17:29.816
ISN'T THAT AMAZING?

17:29.849 --> 17:33.086
THIS MAN, WHO ONLY DAYS AGO
WAS IN THE CLOSET

17:33.120 --> 17:34.721
DEEPER THAN
A LIME-GREEN LEISURE SUIT,

17:34.754 --> 17:39.592
HAS DECIDED TO GO OUT
BECAUSE, UM...

17:39.626 --> 17:42.462
BECAUSE OF ME.

17:42.495 --> 17:44.364
WELL...

17:44.397 --> 17:46.199
I BETTER GET READY.

17:46.233 --> 17:49.369
I'M GOING TO GET A MANICURE
AND A FACIAL.

17:49.402 --> 17:50.570
AND WHO KNOWS?

17:50.603 --> 17:53.106
AFTER, UH,
PAINTING THE TOWN MAUVE,

17:53.140 --> 17:55.175
WE MIGHT JUST END UP
AT BABYLON.

17:55.208 --> 17:57.177
[chuckles]

17:57.210 --> 18:00.347
BYE, MEL.
- OH.

18:09.222 --> 18:11.324
- YOU PLANNING ON HAVING
THAT BABY HERE?

18:11.358 --> 18:13.126
- HUH?

18:13.160 --> 18:15.195
- YOU'VE BEEN SITTING THERE
SINCE BREAKFAST.

18:15.228 --> 18:17.330
HERE'S LUNCH.

18:17.364 --> 18:21.201
- OH, I DIDN'T ORDER THIS.
- I KNOW.

18:21.234 --> 18:25.138
I'M JUST PRACTICING BEING
A LOVING, ATTENTIVE GRANDMA.

18:25.172 --> 18:26.506
- THANKS, DEB.

18:31.178 --> 18:32.379
- NOW I'M GOING TO PRACTICE

18:32.412 --> 18:36.216
BEING A NOSY,
MEDDLESOME GRANDMA.

18:36.249 --> 18:39.819
SOMETHING WRONG, HONEY?
- NO, IT'S NOTHING.

18:39.852 --> 18:43.390
- NOT WITH A PUNIM LIKE THAT.
- HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT WORD?

18:43.423 --> 18:45.425
- YOU LIVE LONG ENOUGH,
EVERYBODY'S JEWISH.

18:50.563 --> 18:52.232
NOTHING'S WRONG
WITH THAT BABY?

18:52.265 --> 18:54.367
- THE BABY'S OKAY.
I'M OKAY.

18:54.401 --> 18:57.270
IT'S NOTHING TO DO WITH THAT.

19:00.673 --> 19:03.643
IT'S LINDSAY AND ME.

19:03.676 --> 19:05.912
WE'RE IN TROUBLE, DEB,
REAL TROUBLE.

19:05.945 --> 19:10.450
- STOP RIGHT THERE.
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW...

19:10.483 --> 19:14.287
'CAUSE WHATEVER IT IS,
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

19:14.321 --> 19:18.525
WHAT MATTERS IS,
YOU'RE ABOUT TO HAVE A BABY.

19:18.558 --> 19:21.194
AND THAT'S ALL THAT COUNTS.

19:21.228 --> 19:24.264
SO IT'S UP TO YOU
TO MAKE THINGS WORK.

19:24.297 --> 19:26.733
SO YOU JUST CHEW ON THAT,

19:26.766 --> 19:28.668
ALONG WITH YOUR CHICKEN SALAD,

19:28.701 --> 19:32.171
WHILE I GRAB YOU A PIECE
OF KEY LIME.

19:35.908 --> 19:38.845
- [sighs]

19:41.848 --> 19:45.485
- AS I SAID, MR. REMSON,
WE'RE A MODEST FACILITY,

19:45.518 --> 19:46.886
TENDING TO THE FINAL NEEDS

19:46.919 --> 19:50.290
OF THOSE FOR WHOM MEDICATIONS
SUCH AS ENDOVIR

19:50.323 --> 19:53.293
HAVE PROVED INEFFECTIVE
OR SIMPLY TOO LATE.

19:53.326 --> 19:56.429
I COUNT MYSELF
AMONG THE FORTUNATE ONES.

19:56.463 --> 19:58.431
- YOU'RE DOING
A HELL OF A JOB HERE.

19:58.465 --> 19:59.866
I'M SURE IT'S NOT EASY.

19:59.899 --> 20:02.602
- THE HARDEST PART
IS NOT BEING ABLE TO DO MORE.

20:02.635 --> 20:05.338
WE'VE ALREADY HAD TO SEND
A COUPLE OF OUR SICKEST CLIENTS

20:05.372 --> 20:06.906
TO THE COUNTY HOSPITAL

20:06.939 --> 20:08.841
SIMPLY BECAUSE WE NO LONGER
HAVE THE STAFF

20:08.875 --> 20:11.644
OR CAPABILITY OF TENDING
TO THEIR NEEDS.

20:11.678 --> 20:13.980
- IT'S A SHAME.
- IT'S MONEY.

20:14.013 --> 20:16.383
STATE FUNDING
HAS BEEN REDUCED.

20:16.416 --> 20:18.785
PRIVATE DONATIONS
HAVE ALL BUT DRIED UP,

20:18.818 --> 20:19.852
DUE TO THE MISCONCEPTION

20:19.886 --> 20:22.322
THAT NO ONE DIES OF AIDS
ANYMORE.

20:22.355 --> 20:25.858
- WELL, I HOPE YOU MANAGE
TO FIND THE NECESSARY FUNDS.

20:25.892 --> 20:28.595
- IT MAY BE TOO LATE FOR THAT.

20:28.628 --> 20:31.998
LIKE OUR CLIENTS,
WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

20:32.031 --> 20:34.601
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I HAVE TO GO BACK TO WORK.

20:34.634 --> 20:37.570
THERE ARE ONLY TWO OF US.

20:42.375 --> 20:44.677
- I SUPPOSE YOU'RE GOING
TO HIT ME UP NOW.

20:44.711 --> 20:46.346
AND AFTER WHAT
I'VE JUST SEEN,

20:46.379 --> 20:48.415
IT'S GOING TO BE VERY HARD
TO SAY NO.

20:48.448 --> 20:51.484
- IT'S A WORTHY CAUSE.
- THEY'RE ALL WORTHY CAUSES.

20:51.518 --> 20:53.353
- ALL I'M ASKING
IS FOR YOU TO SPONSOR

20:53.386 --> 20:55.021
ONE RIDER
IN THE LIBERTY RIDE.

20:55.054 --> 20:57.023
- THAT'S IT?
- THAT'S IT.

20:57.056 --> 20:59.392
- WELL, I SUPPOSE
WE CAN HANDLE THAT.

20:59.426 --> 21:01.894
- HOW MUCH DO YOU WANT?
- $100,000.

21:01.928 --> 21:04.531
LOOK, IT'S NO MORE THAN YOU'D
SPEND FOR AN AD IN A MAGAZINE,

21:04.564 --> 21:06.799
AND THINK OF THE GOODWILL
YOU'LL BE GENERATING.

21:06.833 --> 21:09.569
IT'S MORE THAN ANY CAMPAIGN
THAT I COULD COME UP WITH.

21:09.602 --> 21:11.638
AS FOR THE RIDER
YOU'LL BE SPONSORING,

21:11.671 --> 21:15.675
HE'S AN AMAZING ATHLETE
AND A RENOWNED HUMANITARIAN.

21:19.446 --> 21:22.382
- WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU DOING--
BRAIN SURGERY?

21:22.415 --> 21:24.784
- FAR MORE DELICATE.

21:24.817 --> 21:28.521
THIS IS A VERY RARE COMIC
FROM THE '50s.

21:28.555 --> 21:31.658
AND YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO LET
THE ACID FROM YOUR FINGERS

21:31.691 --> 21:35.061
TOUCH THE PAPER.

21:35.094 --> 21:36.663
THERE.

21:36.696 --> 21:38.665
THE OPERATION IS A SUCCESS.

21:38.698 --> 21:42.335
MICHAEL NOVOTNY, DOCTOR
OF COMICOLOGY, TRIUMPHS AGAIN.

21:42.369 --> 21:43.703
- FREAK SHOW.

21:43.736 --> 21:45.938
[phone rings]
- WOULD YOU GET THAT?

21:45.972 --> 21:49.342
AND TELL WHOEVER IT IS
THAT THE DOCTOR IS IN.

21:49.376 --> 21:52.078
[phone rings]

21:52.111 --> 21:54.080
- HELLO?

21:54.113 --> 21:56.549
UH, SURE.
HOLD ON.

21:56.583 --> 21:58.685
IT'S MR. LEESON...

21:58.718 --> 21:59.952
CALLIE'S DAD.

21:59.986 --> 22:01.921
- OH.

22:03.856 --> 22:05.558
STEVE? HI.

22:05.592 --> 22:07.827
IT WAS NICE MEETING YOU
AND AMBER THE OTHER NIGHT.

22:07.860 --> 22:10.963
BEN AND I ARE REALLY LOOKING
FORWARD TO GETTING TOGETHER.

22:10.997 --> 22:12.365
TONIGHT?

22:12.399 --> 22:13.566
WELL, I'LL HAVE TO CHECK
WITH BEN,

22:13.600 --> 22:14.601
BUT I'M SURE IT'LL BE OKAY.

22:14.634 --> 22:17.737
WHERE WOULD YOU LIKE TO MEET?

22:17.770 --> 22:21.708
THAT'D BE FINE.
HOW ABOUT 8:00?

22:21.741 --> 22:23.710
SEE YOU THEN.

22:23.743 --> 22:24.977
- WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

22:25.011 --> 22:26.479
- WE'D BETTER GO HOME
AND DUST.

22:26.513 --> 22:29.482
YOUR IN-LAWS-TO-BE
ARE COMING OVER.

