I'D SAY THAT WE WERE

23:19.799 --> 23:22.569
WELL INTO
THE QUADRUPLE DIGITS...

23:22.602 --> 23:24.036
[groans]

23:24.070 --> 23:27.540
THAT HAS TO RANK
IN THE TOP FIVE.

23:27.574 --> 23:31.110
- GOOD.
THAT'LL BE $1,000, PLEASE.

23:31.143 --> 23:34.180
- THAT'S QUITE AN INCREASE
FROM THE TWO BITS

23:34.213 --> 23:36.916
YOU WERE CHARGING
WHEN WE MET.

23:36.949 --> 23:39.786
- TO EXPERIENCE PERFECTION
IS A PRIVILEGE

23:39.819 --> 23:41.954
REGARDLESS OF THE PRICE.

23:41.988 --> 23:44.791
- BESIDES, I NEED YOU TO SPONSOR
ME FOR THE LIBERTY RIDE.

23:44.824 --> 23:46.092
- I'M SORRY, SUNSHINE.

23:46.125 --> 23:48.561
I'M ALREADY SPONSORING
SOMEONE ELSE.

23:48.595 --> 23:49.996
ME.

23:50.029 --> 23:51.831
- WHAT?

23:51.864 --> 23:53.833
- I'M DOING THE RIDE.

23:53.866 --> 23:55.935
- YOU CAN'T DO THE RIDE.

23:55.968 --> 23:57.937
YOU'VE BARELY RECOVERED.

23:57.970 --> 24:01.107
THE DOCTOR TOLD YOU TO TAKE IT
EASY, AND AT YOUR AGE--

24:01.140 --> 24:05.845
- AT MY AGE,
I CAN MAKE UP MY OWN MIND.

24:05.878 --> 24:09.616
- YOU HATE BICYCLING.
YOU DESPISE CAMPING OUT.

24:09.649 --> 24:11.718
YOU DETEST
ANY AND ALL FORMS OF CHARITY.

24:11.751 --> 24:13.119
YOU LOATHE
THE GAY AND LESBIAN CENTER

24:13.152 --> 24:15.555
AND EVERYONE
ASSOCIATED WITH IT.

24:15.588 --> 24:18.591
SO GIVE ME ONE--
JUST ONE GOOD REASON WHY.

24:18.625 --> 24:21.260
- I WANT TO.

24:21.293 --> 24:25.698
- WELL, YOU CAN'T.

24:25.732 --> 24:28.601
YOU HAVEN'T TRAINED.
YOU'RE NOT IN SHAPE.

24:28.635 --> 24:29.969
THERE'S NO WAY YOU'D MAKE IT
OUT OF TORONTO,

24:30.002 --> 24:33.105
MUCH LESS THE 322 MILES
BACK TO PITTSBURGH.

24:33.139 --> 24:36.576
- YOUR PROPHECIES OF DOOM
ONLY INCITE ME MORE.

24:36.609 --> 24:37.910
- I'M JUST BEING REALISTIC.

24:37.944 --> 24:41.147
- WELL, WE DREAMERS
HAVE NO TIME FOR THAT.

24:43.883 --> 24:46.252
WHEN'S THE NEXT SPIN CLASS?
- TOMORROW.

24:46.285 --> 24:48.020
- HMM.

24:48.054 --> 24:50.256
WITH A LITTLE PRACTICE,

24:50.289 --> 24:52.892
I'LL FLY LIKE THE WIND.

24:54.894 --> 24:56.863
- UGH.

24:56.896 --> 24:59.799
- [clears throat]

25:04.236 --> 25:07.607
THE SALMON WAS DELICIOUS.

25:07.640 --> 25:09.075
- THANKS.

25:09.108 --> 25:11.778
I TRIED TO COOK IT THE WAY
YOU LIKE, ALMOST RARE.

25:11.811 --> 25:14.313
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME MORE?
- NO, THANKS.

25:14.346 --> 25:15.782
- HERE, LET ME.
- NO, NO, NO.

25:15.815 --> 25:18.651
YOU COOKED, I'LL CLEAN UP.

25:20.086 --> 25:22.789
THE PREMIUM FOR
THE VARIABLE ANNUITY ARRIVED,

25:22.822 --> 25:25.224
WE BOTH HAVE TO WRITE CHECKS.

25:25.257 --> 25:27.159
AND THE TERMITE INSPECTOR'S
COMING TOMORROW.

25:27.193 --> 25:29.161
- IT NEVER STOPS, DOES IT?
- WHAT?

25:29.195 --> 25:30.963
- THE HOUSE,
KEEPING THINGS IN ORDER.

25:30.997 --> 25:32.832
IF IT ISN'T ONE THING,
IT'S ANOTHER.

25:32.865 --> 25:35.334
- WE DON'T WANT
THE FOUNDATION TO ROT.

25:35.367 --> 25:36.769
- NO, WE DON'T.

25:36.803 --> 25:39.639
- THEN WE HAVE
TO TAKE CARE OF IT.

25:39.672 --> 25:42.575
AFTER ALL, IT'S OUR HOME.

25:45.111 --> 25:47.179
SUSANNAH CALLED,

25:47.213 --> 25:50.717
ABOUT THOSE TICKETS
TO THE EVGENY KISSIN RECITAL.

25:50.750 --> 25:52.218
SHE WANTED TO KNOW IF WE'RE
STILL PLANNING ON GOING

25:52.251 --> 25:53.586
WITH HER AND TESS.

25:53.620 --> 25:54.721
I SAID, OF COURSE.

25:54.754 --> 25:57.690
- OH, MEL.

25:58.991 --> 26:00.927
- [sighs]

26:00.960 --> 26:02.729
JUST STOP IT.

26:02.762 --> 26:05.131
STOP IT!

26:05.164 --> 26:08.067
- WHAT?

26:08.100 --> 26:10.336
I JUST WANTED TO GIVE YOU
A HUG AND A KISS.

26:10.369 --> 26:14.607
- WELL, I DON'T WANT YOU
GIVING ME A HUG OR A KISS.

26:14.641 --> 26:16.709
BUT I THOUGHT--
I MEAN...

26:16.743 --> 26:18.344
THAT EVERYTHING
WAS GOING TO BE OKAY.

26:18.377 --> 26:21.814
- HOW COULD EVERYTHING
BE OKAY?

26:21.848 --> 26:23.950
I'M JUST TRYING TO MAINTAIN
SOME SENSE OF ORDER,

26:23.983 --> 26:26.919
JUST HOLD THINGS TOGETHER.

26:29.188 --> 26:32.959
- I SEE.

26:32.992 --> 26:36.228
I ACTUALLY THOUGHT
YOU DECIDED TO FORGIVE ME.

26:36.262 --> 26:39.732
- YOU MUST EXPECT MIRACLES
OR AMNESIA.

26:39.766 --> 26:41.834
WELL, I'M SORRY I CAN'T
GIVE YOU WHAT YOU WANT.

26:41.868 --> 26:44.003
BUT THAT'S PAR
FOR THE COURSE, ISN'T IT?

26:44.036 --> 26:45.872
- WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

26:45.905 --> 26:48.741
- THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO

26:48.775 --> 26:51.911
THAT'LL EVER MAKE YOU
FEEL COMPLETELY HAPPY.

26:51.944 --> 26:53.412
YOU'LL ALWAYS
FEEL UNSATISFIED,

26:53.445 --> 26:55.047
AND I'LL ALWAYS
FEEL LIKE I'M NOT ENOUGH.

26:55.081 --> 26:56.716
- THAT'S NOT TRUE.

26:56.749 --> 26:58.117
- OH, BULLSHIT!
OF COURSE IT IS.

26:58.150 --> 26:59.986
OTHERWISE, NONE OF THIS
WOULD'VE HAPPENED.

27:00.019 --> 27:03.723
- MEL!
[sighs]

27:03.756 --> 27:07.193
- OOH!
- MEL?

27:07.226 --> 27:09.395
ARE YOU OKAY?

27:09.428 --> 27:12.164
- SOMETHING FEELS WRONG.
- OH, GOD.

